Full dataset for chapter 4 on lumpfish livers

fullc4 <- read_excel("DATA_COMPILED_18JAN2022_chapter3.xlsx")
liverdata <-fullc4 %>%
  filter(tissue=="liver")
liverdata1 <- liverdata %>% 
  filter(weight<150)
liverdata1$site2<-factor(liverdata1$site2, ordered = TRUE)
 fullc4$livscore<-factor(fullc4$livscore, ordered = TRUE,levels = 1:6)
 
arcsine_transform <- function(x) {
  asin(sqrt(x / 100))  # Transform percentage to proportion and apply arcsine
}
livlip_transformed <- liverdata1 %>%
  mutate(across(c(41), ~ arcsine_transform(.)))

Boxplot and linear model to assess the effect of origin on hepatosomatic index (HSI), evaluate the model with ANOVA, perform Tukey’s post hoc test, and generate compact letter display for group comparisons

ggplot(liverdata, aes(x = site2, y = hsi)) +
  geom_boxplot(color = "black") +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.2, alpha = 0.6, size = 1) +  # Add data points
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    text = element_text(size = 14),
    plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = 16, hjust = 0.5),
    legend.position = "none"
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "Origin",
    y = "HSI",
  )

Plot of liver colour frequency data as a stacked bar chart, comparing wild, sea cage, and land-based origins.

Colorus represent liver colour categories. Data from Excel

# Data
data <- matrix(c(
  0.07843137, 0.04878049, 0.02702703,
  0.03921569, 0.05691057, 0.21621622,
  0.09803922, 0.07317073, 0.43243243,
  0.74509804, 0.75609756, 0.32432432,
  0.03921569, 0.04065041, 0,
  0, 0.02439024, 0
), ncol=3, byrow=TRUE)

# Convert to percentages
data <- data * 100

# Assign column names
colnames(data) <- c("Wild", "Sea cage", "Land Based")
rownames(data) <- 1:6

# Custom colors (6 colors now since we removed a row)
custom_colors <- c("#F0E3AF", "#FCCC7B", "#FFA578", "#FF7F26", "#C56F58", "#AC5430")

# Layout for plot and legend with adjusted widths
layout(matrix(c(1,2), ncol=2), widths=c(15,1))

# Plotting the stacked bar plot with y-axis limited to 100
barplot(data, beside=FALSE, main="Liver colour frequencies", ylab="Percentage (%)", xlab="Origin", col=custom_colors, border="white", ylim=c(0, 100))

# Adding the legend in the second layout area without a title
par(mar=c(0,0,0,0))
plot.new()
legend("center", legend=rownames(data), fill=custom_colors, cex=1, bty="n")

Table of fatty acids, including arcsin transformation, mean and standard deviation, lm statistics and letters

fattyacidsToTest = c("a14:0", "a16:0","a18:0","SAFA", "16:1n-7", "18:1n-9", "18:1n-7", "20:1n-9","22:1n-11", "MUFA", "18:2n-6", "20:4n-6", "n-6 PUFA", "18:3n-3", "18:4n-3", "20:5n-3","22:5n-3", "22:6n-3", "n-3 PUFA","Tot PUFA", "LC-PUFA","EPA/DHA", "EPA+DHA", "EPA_g/100g", "DPA_g/100g","DHA_g/100g","EPA+DHA_g/100g", "EPA+DPA+DHA_g/100g")


liv_fa_transformed <- liverdata1 %>%
  mutate(across(c(72:117, 151:156), ~ arcsine_transform(.)))

results <- list()
letters <- list()

calculate_stats <- function(data, fattyacid) {
  mean_val <- mean(data[[fattyacid]], na.rm = TRUE)
  sd_val <- sd(data[[fattyacid]], na.rm = TRUE)
  mean_sd <- paste0(round(mean_val, 1), " ± ", round(sd_val, 1))
  return(c(mean = round(mean_val, 3), sd = round(sd_val, 3), mean_sd = mean_sd))
}

format_p_value <- function(p_value) {
  if (p_value < 0.001) {
    return("P<0.001")
  } else {
    return(round(p_value, 5))
  }
}

# Loop through each fatty acid
for (fattyacid in fattyacidsToTest) {
  # Create the formula with both site2, weight, and their interaction as predictors
  formula <- as.formula(paste0("`", fattyacid, "` ~ site2 * weight"))
  
  # Fit the linear model
  mod <- lm(formula, data = liv_fa_transformed)
  
  # Extract p-values for site2, weight, and their interaction
  p_value_site2 <- format_p_value(anova(mod)["site2", "Pr(>F)"])
  p_value_weight <- format_p_value(anova(mod)["weight", "Pr(>F)"])
  p_value_interaction <- format_p_value(anova(mod)["site2:weight", "Pr(>F)"])
  
  # Calculate R-squared value
  r_squared <- round(r2(mod)$R2, 3)

  # Extract F-statistic
  f_stat <- summary(mod)$fstatistic
  f_stat_string <- paste0(round(f_stat["value"], 2), " on ", f_stat["numdf"], " and ", f_stat["dendf"], " DF")
  
  # Perform Tukey post-hoc test and calculate significance letters
  anova_model <- aov(as.formula(paste0("`", fattyacid, "` ~ site2")), data = liv_fa_transformed)
  tmp <- -1
  tryCatch({
    tukey <- TukeyHSD(anova_model)
    cld_results <- glht(anova_model, linfct = mcp(site2 = "Tukey"))
    tmp <- cld(cld_results, level = 0.10)$mcletters$Letters
    tukey_wild <- tmp["wild"]
    tukey_sea_cage <- tmp["sea cage"]
    tukey_land_based <- tmp["land based"]
  }, error = function(e) {
    tukey_wild <- tukey_sea_cage <- tukey_land_based <- NA
  })
  
  # Append the letters to the list
  letters[[fattyacid]] <- tmp

  # Calculate stats for the full dataset
  all_stats <- calculate_stats(liverdata1, fattyacid)
  
  # Calculate stats for each site2 category
  wild_stats <- calculate_stats(liverdata1[liverdata1$site2 == "wild", ], fattyacid)
  sea_cage_stats <- calculate_stats(liverdata1[liverdata1$site2 == "sea cage", ], fattyacid)
  land_based_stats <- calculate_stats(liverdata1[liverdata1$site2 == "land based", ], fattyacid)
  
  # Append the results to the list as a named vector
  results[[fattyacid]] <- c(
    fattyacid = fattyacid,
    all_stats,
    p_site2 = p_value_site2,
    p_weight = p_value_weight,
    p_interaction = p_value_interaction,
    r_squared = r_squared,
    f_statistic = f_stat_string,
    tukey_wild = tmp["wild"],
    tukey_sea_cage = tmp["sea cage"],
    tukey_land_based = tmp["land based"],
    wild_mean = wild_stats["mean"],
    wild_sd = wild_stats["sd"],
    wild_mean_sd = wild_stats["mean_sd"],
    sea_cage_mean = sea_cage_stats["mean"],
    sea_cage_sd = sea_cage_stats["sd"],
    sea_cage_mean_sd = sea_cage_stats["mean_sd"],
    land_based_mean = land_based_stats["mean"],
    land_based_sd = land_based_stats["sd"],
    land_based_mean_sd = land_based_stats["mean_sd"]
  )
}

# Convert the results list to a properly structured data frame
results_df <- do.call(rbind, results) %>%
  as.data.frame(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Ensure columns are correctly named

  "Mean (All)", "Standard Deviation (All)", "Mean ± SD (All)",
  "P-value (site2, All)", "P-value (weight, All)", "P-value (interaction, All)",
  "R-squared", "F-statistic",
  "Tukey (Wild)", "Tukey (Sea Cage)", "Tukey (Land Based)",

  "Mean (Sea Cage)", "Standard Deviation (Sea Cage)", "Mean ± SD (Sea Cage)",

)

Table of total carotenoids, including arcsin transformation, mean and standard deviation, lm statistics and letters

# Define your fatty acid variables
fattyacidsToTest = c("Astaxanthin", "Canthaxanthin", "Lutein", "Astacene", "Astaxanthin esters", "Beta-carotene",
                     "totalcarotenoids")

# Subset for small fish
liver_small <- liverdata %>% filter(weight < 950)

# Ensure site2 is a factor
liver_small$site2 <- as.factor(liver_small$site2)

# Apply arcsine transformation safely to columns 46–53
liverdata_transformed <- liver_small %>%
  mutate(across(c(46:53), ~ asin(sqrt(pmin(pmax(. / 100, 0), 1)))))

# Also set factor in transformed data
liverdata_transformed$site2 <- as.factor(liverdata_transformed$site2)

# Format p-value safely
format_p_value <- function(p_value) {
  if (is.na(p_value)) {
    return("NA")
  } else if (p_value < 0.001) {
    return("P<0.001")
  } else {
    return(round(p_value, 5))
  }
}

# Helper: calculate mean, sd, and formatted string
calculate_stats <- function(data, fattyacid) {
  mean_val <- mean(data[[fattyacid]], na.rm = TRUE)
  sd_val <- sd(data[[fattyacid]], na.rm = TRUE)
  mean_sd <- paste0(round(mean_val, 1), " ± ", round(sd_val, 1))
  return(c(mean = round(mean_val, 3), sd = round(sd_val, 3), mean_sd = mean_sd))
}

# Results containers
results <- list()
letters <- list()

# Loop through fatty acids
for (fattyacid in fattyacidsToTest) {
  formula <- as.formula(paste0("`", fattyacid, "` ~ site2 * weight"))
  mod <- lm(formula, data = liverdata_transformed)
  
  # P-values
  p_value_site2 <- format_p_value(anova(mod)["site2", "Pr(>F)"])
  p_value_weight <- format_p_value(anova(mod)["weight", "Pr(>F)"])
  p_value_interaction <- format_p_value(anova(mod)["site2:weight", "Pr(>F)"])
  
  # R2 and F-statistic
  r_squared <- round(r2(mod)$R2, 3)
  f_stat <- summary(mod)$fstatistic
  f_stat_string <- paste0(round(f_stat["value"], 2), " on ", f_stat["numdf"], " and ", f_stat["dendf"], " DF")
  
  # Tukey post-hoc test and CLD letters
  anova_model <- aov(as.formula(paste0("`", fattyacid, "` ~ site2")), data = liverdata_transformed)
  tmp <- -1
  tryCatch({
    tukey <- glht(anova_model, linfct = mcp(site2 = "Tukey"))
    cld_results <- cld(tukey, level = 0.10)$mcletters$Letters
    tukey_wild <- cld_results["wild"]
    tukey_sea_cage <- cld_results["sea cage"]
    tukey_land_based <- cld_results["land based"]
  }, error = function(e) {
    tukey_wild <- tukey_sea_cage <- tukey_land_based <- NA
  })
  
  letters[[fattyacid]] <- cld_results

  # Stats
  all_stats <- calculate_stats(liverdata, fattyacid)
  wild_stats <- calculate_stats(liver_small[liver_small$site2 == "wild", ], fattyacid)
  sea_cage_stats <- calculate_stats(liver_small[liver_small$site2 == "sea cage", ], fattyacid)
  land_based_stats <- calculate_stats(liver_small[liver_small$site2 == "land based", ], fattyacid)
  
  # Combine
  results[[fattyacid]] <- c(
    fattyacid = fattyacid,
    all_stats,
    p_site2 = p_value_site2,
    p_weight = p_value_weight,
    p_interaction = p_value_interaction,
    r_squared = r_squared,
    f_statistic = f_stat_string,
    tukey_wild = tukey_wild,
    tukey_sea_cage = tukey_sea_cage,
    tukey_land_based = tukey_land_based,
    wild_mean = wild_stats["mean"],
    wild_sd = wild_stats["sd"],
    wild_mean_sd = wild_stats["mean_sd"],
    sea_cage_mean = sea_cage_stats["mean"],
    sea_cage_sd = sea_cage_stats["sd"],
    sea_cage_mean_sd = sea_cage_stats["mean_sd"],
    land_based_mean = land_based_stats["mean"],
    land_based_sd = land_based_stats["sd"],
    land_based_mean_sd = land_based_stats["mean_sd"]
  )
}

# Convert to data frame
results_df <- do.call(rbind, results) %>%
  as.data.frame(stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Rename columns
colnames(results_df) <- c(
  "Fatty Acid",
  "Mean (All)", "Standard Deviation (All)", "Mean ± SD (All)",
  "P-value (site2, All)", "P-value (weight, All)", "P-value (interaction, All)",
  "R-squared", "F-statistic",
  "Tukey (Wild)", "Tukey (Sea Cage)", "Tukey (Land Based)",
  "Mean (Wild)", "Standard Deviation (Wild)", "Mean ± SD (Wild)",
  "Mean (Sea Cage)", "Standard Deviation (Sea Cage)", "Mean ± SD (Sea Cage)",
  "Mean (Land Based)", "Standard Deviation (Land Based)", "Mean ± SD (Land Based)"
)

# Save to Excel
write.xlsx(results_df, file = "pigdata_filteredwithletters.xlsx", rowNames = FALSE)
